# Files chezmoi deletes from the target on `chezmoi apply`, on every machine.
# Used to retire the old split SSH-config layout now that ~/.ssh/config is the
# single tracked config.
#
# NOTE: deliberately does NOT list private key files. Removing those is gated on
# verifying the 1Password agent serves the consolidated keys first — see the
# ssh-consolidation runbook. Auto-removing a private key before the agent is
# ready would lock you out.
.config/ssh/config
.config/ssh/config.local
